    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban local councils from charging for rubble and diy waste materials",
        "additional_details": "\u00a33 per bag of waste means the average kitchen or bathroom renovation could easily cost \u00a3150 for waste. People have paid their councils to provide local waste facilities and this charge is undoubtedly leading to fly tipping as well as penalising those who cannot afford to employ a tradesman.",
        "background": "Force local councils to remove charges applied for waste from diy projects. This would include \r\nCeramic \r\nPaving \r\nWood \r\nWood derivatives\r\nCement",
